[2] Illinois, Algonquin
Date: Wed 7 Jun 2017 7:23 PM
Source: Daily Herald [edited]
http://www.dailyherald.com/news/20170607/officials-3-more-jacobs-high-students-test-positive-for-mumps


A total of 3 more Jacobs High School students have tested positive for mumps, bringing the number of confirmed cases in the district to 6, school officials announced [Wed 7 Jun 2017].

All 6 students previously had been vaccinated, according to a news release from Community Unit District 300.

The 3 students who most recently tested positive for mumps went to class through the last day of school, which was 25 May [2017], the release said.

Students and staff members who are not vaccinated or have compromised immune systems have been kept out of the school since 15 May [2017], when the 1st student tested positive for mumps.

None of the 3 students who recently tested positive shared classes, athletics or activities within the school setting, school officials said.

The school district, along with the health departments in Kane and McHenry counties, is monitoring the cases.

Mumps symptoms include fever, headache, muscle aches, tiredness, loss of appetite and swollen glands, according to the Kane County Health Department.

[Byline: Katie Smith]

